20. What is a Subquery?

Answer

A Subquery in MySQL is a query written inside another query.

The inner query executes first, and its result is used by the outer query.

Subqueries are commonly used with SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, and DELETE statements.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Features of Subquery

• Query inside another query
• Also called Nested Query
• Executes from inner query to outer query
• Helps perform complex operations easily
• Can be used with WHERE, FROM, and HAVING clauses

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Syntax of Subquery

SELECT column_name
FROM table_name
WHERE column_name operator (
    SELECT column_name
    FROM table_name
    WHERE condition
);

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Example of Subquery

SELECT employee_name
FROM employees
WHERE salary > (
    SELECT AVG(salary)
    FROM employees
);

Explanation

• Inner query finds average salary.
• Outer query displays employees whose salary is greater than average salary.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Real-Time Example

Consider an Employee Table.

Employee_Name      Department      Salary
Rahul              IT              60000
Priya              HR              45000
Arjun              IT              70000
Sneha              Finance         55000
Kiran              IT              65000

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Subquery Example

SELECT employee_name
FROM employees
WHERE salary > (
    SELECT AVG(salary)
    FROM employees
);

Output

Rahul
Arjun
Kiran

Explanation

• Average salary is 59000.
• Employees earning more than average salary are displayed.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Types of Subqueries

Single Row Subquery
• Returns only one row

Multiple Row Subquery
• Returns multiple rows

Correlated Subquery
• Depends on outer query for execution

Nested Subquery
• Contains another subquery inside it

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Subquery with IN Operator

SELECT employee_name
FROM employees
WHERE department IN (
    SELECT department
    FROM departments
    WHERE location = 'Hyderabad'
);

Explanation

• Displays employees working in departments located in Hyderabad.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Important Points

• Subquery is written inside parentheses ().
• Inner query executes before outer query.
• Used to simplify complex SQL queries.
• Can return single or multiple rows.
• Commonly used with SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, and DELETE statements.

